A restaurant in Johannesburg is among thousands affected by the COVID-19 outbreak. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Many restaurants are still battling to get payouts from insurers for losses suffered through business interruptions. Most have been forced to approach the courts for relief. WATCH: UK imposes flight restrictions on South Africa This is despite the Appeals court affirmation of a High Court decision that found in favour of a Cape Town restaurant which took legal action against insurer Guardrisk. eNCA's Manqoba Mchunu looks at the plight of restaurateurs. Watch the video above.